#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:27
msgid ""
"Languages follow ISO 639-1 — currently `en`, `nl`, `de`. Organization is an "
"open-ended string; existing values include `flevoland`, `toeslagen`, `bzk`, "
"`ind`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:31
msgid "List panel toolbar"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:33
msgid ""
"Each editor's list panel (BPMN Modeler, Form Editor, Document Composer) "
"shares the same toolbar:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:35
msgid ""
"**Search** — free text matches against name, description, and the artefact's "
"identifier (BPMN process id, form schema id, document process key)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:36
msgid ""
"**Language filter** — `All languages` (default), `Untagged`, or a specific "
"code (English, Dutch, German). Untagged artefacts always match the All "
"filter and only appear when Untagged is selected."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:37
msgid ""
"**Match counter** — `<matched>/<total>` shown next to the filter when both "
"numbers are useful"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:39
msgid ""
"A live count appears next to the language filter so you can see at a glance "
"how many of your artefacts match the current filter."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:43
msgid "Collapsible organization groups"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:45
msgid ""
"Below the toolbar, artefacts are grouped under collapsible organization "
"headers (FLEVOLAND, TOESLAGEN, BZK, etc.). Untagged artefacts go to an "
"UNGROUPED group at the bottom. Click a header to collapse or expand the "
"group."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:47
msgid ""
"For BPMN, subprocesses follow their shell's organization regardless of their "
"own tag — so a Tree Felling subprocess shows under FLEVOLAND together with "
"its AWB shell, even if the subprocess itself has no organization tag."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:49
msgid ""
"If a subprocess's shell is hidden by the active filter (e.g. you've filtered "
"to language=nl and the shell is English), the subprocess renders as a flat "
"orphan card rather than disappearing."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:53
msgid "Editor footer panel"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:55
msgid ""
"Each editor (BPMN Modeler, Form Editor, Document Composer) shares the same "
"footer pattern. Selecting an artefact opens a footer panel below the list "
"with the metadata selectors:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:57
msgid ""
"**Language** — dropdown with Language-agnostic / English / Dutch / German"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:58
msgid ""
"**Organization** — text input with autocomplete from existing organization "
"keys"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:59
msgid "(BPMN only) **RoPA Record** — link to a GDPR Art. 30 record"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:60
msgid "(BPMN only) **DSO Activity** — verify and link a DSO activiteit URN"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:67
msgid ""
"The same footer pattern, scoped to language and organization only, appears "
"in the Form Editor and Document Composer."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:71
msgid "Pending-until-Save model"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:73
msgid ""
"Footer edits are pending until you click **Save** — they no longer write "
"through immediately. While you're typing in the organization field, the "
"artefact does not regroup in the list panel. Save commits all pending "
"changes (canvas content plus footer metadata) atomically and the list "
"updates."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:75
msgid ""
"If you try to navigate away from an artefact with unsaved changes, a confirm "
"prompt asks whether to discard them. Cancel keeps you on the artefact; OK "
"discards the draft and proceeds."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:77
msgid ""
"For BPMN shells, saving propagates the shell's `language` and `organization` "
"to all linked subprocesses in the same atomic write — so an AWB shell saved "
"with `nl` / `flevoland` pulls the Tree Felling subprocess to the same values "
"automatically. Shell wins unconditionally; example subprocesses (`readonly: "
"true`) are skipped."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:81
msgid "Filename-based language inference on import"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:83
msgid ""
"Drop a `.bpmn`, `.form`, or `.document` file with a language suffix in its "
"name (e.g. `capacity-claim-intake.nl.form`) into the import button — LDE "
"picks up the suffix and tags the imported artefact automatically. Order of "
"precedence:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:85
msgid ""
"Language baked into the file (`ronl:language` in BPMN XML, top-level "
"`language` key in form/document JSON)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:86
msgid "Filename suffix `.<lang>.<ext>`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:87
msgid "Untagged"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:89
msgid ""
"The form export reciprocates: clicking **Export .form** wraps the form-js "
"schema with the language and organization at the top of the exported JSON "
"and uses a language-suffixed filename. Re-importing that file populates both "
"fields automatically."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:93
msgid "Deploy-time language consistency check"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:95
msgid ""
"When you open the **Deploy** modal on a BPMN bundle, LDE walks the resources "
"(shell BPMN + subprocess BPMNs + linked forms + linked documents) and "
"collects all distinct language tags. If more than one is present, an amber "
"warning appears inline in the modal listing the offending codes:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:102
msgid ""
"The warning is non-blocking — Deploy stays enabled. It mirrors the existing "
"RoPA-missing warning UX. DMNs are not part of the check because they're "
"language-agnostic by design."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:106
msgid "HR-capacity Dutch reference bundle"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:108
msgid "The first multi-language reference bundle ships with v1.6.0:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:110
msgid ""
"`Beheer capaciteitsclaim — proces (Voorbeeld, NL)` — 1 BPMN, 8 forms, 2 "
"documents"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:111
msgid "All artefacts tagged `language=nl`, `organization=flevoland`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:112
msgid ""
"Same `CapacityClaimRouting` DMN serves both the English and Dutch siblings — "
"variable keys (`requestType`, `decisionRoute`, `advisoryGroup`, etc.) stay "
"stable English; only labels and option text are translated"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:113
msgid ""
"All `formRef` and `documentRef` values in the Dutch BPMN are suffixed `-nl` "
"to point at the Dutch siblings"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:115
msgid ""
"Open the BPMN under FLEVOLAND, walk the canvas, open the linked forms — "
"every label, description, button, and option label is in Dutch; behind the "
"scenes the variable keys and DMN logic are unchanged from the English "
"version."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:119
msgid "Known limitation — form-js properties panel focus loss"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:121
msgid ""
"When editing properties in the Form Editor (Field label, Description, Key), "
"the input loses focus when you pause typing. This is upstream form-js issue "
"#86, marked wontfix by bpmn-io — the form-js properties panel rebuilds "
"itself on its own debounced commit, which loses the active input focus. It "
"is not caused by LDE and not fixable from React without forking form-js."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cmultilingualism.md:123
msgid ""
"Workaround: edit the `.form` JSON directly in a code editor and re-import. "
"Filename-based language inference handles the language tagging automatically."
msgstr ""

